sequenceDiagram
    participant OS as Operating System
    participant App as Application
    participant Socket as Unix Socket
    participant Config as Config Directory

    App->>Config: Get Application Config Directory
    App->>Config: Create Config Directory (if needed)
    App->>Socket: Check if socket file exists

    alt Socket File Exists
        App->>Socket: Connect to existing socket
        alt Connection Successful
            App->>Socket: Send arguments as JSON
            Socket-->>App: Acknowledgement
            App->>OS: Exit Application
        else Connection Failed (Dead Socket)
            App->>Socket: Delete dead socket file
            App->>Socket: Create new Unix socket
            App->>App: Listen for incoming connections
            App->>App: Return True (First instance)
        end
    else Socket File Does Not Exist
        App->>Socket: Create new Unix socket
        App->>App: Listen for incoming connections
        App->>App: Return True (First instance)
    end

    loop Listen for incoming connections
        Socket->>App: Connection from second instance
        App->>Socket: Read incoming JSON arguments
        App->>App: Decode JSON arguments
        App->>App: Call cmdProcessor with decoded arguments
    end
